			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">I think the size increase is OK.  This just makes x86-32 consistent with x86-64.

Using "-fomit-frame-pointer" is not so good because it could have a performance impact.

In the longer term we may want to expose IRT unwind information so that an untrusted crash reporter can unwind the stack on the client side, and I don't think such a crash reporter should have to fall back to guessing about stack frames like GDB does.  So adding dynamic unwind info is the right direction to go in.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-08-29T17:03:37.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-08-29T17:03:37.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 4 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3005#c4" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3005/comments/full/4" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>